        "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
        "score": 8,
        "is_accepted": true,
        "last_activity_date": 1513765129,
        "creation_date": 1513689597,
        "body": "<p>Actually NO, but you can use the following code:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>ChronoUnit.DAYS.between(from, to) + 1;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p><code>+1<\/code> adds 1 day to the difference between those two local dates so we can say that the last date is included.<\/p>\n",
        "answer_id": 47887956,
